Package: isolation
Title: Model Transmission Potential Averted by Isolation Guidance
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(
    person("Eric", "Mooring", , "pgv5@cdc.gov", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Guido", "España", role = c("aut")),
    person("Chirag", "Kumar", role = "aut")
  )
Description: A model of the effects of isolation and post-isolation
    precautions on reducing potential for onward transmission of COVID-19.
    Transmission potential is assumed to be time-varying based on viral
    load "triangles" and antigen and culture assay positivity. Model
    compares updated CDC respiratory pathogen guidance that was
    implemented on March 1, 2024 to the previous guidance. In this code
    base, the updated guidance is referred to as "proposed" and the
    previous guidance referred to as "current". This model only considers
    individual-level reductions in transmission potential; it does not
    model population-level dynamic effects of isolation.
